      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The high-pitched squealing sound when braking is quite a common issue, and I'm here to help you troubleshoot it. It's possible that the sound is coming from the front passenger side brake caliper or the brake pads themselves. You might want to check the brake pads and rotors for wear, as worn-out brake components can cause unusual noises when braking. It's also possible that the sound is related to the brake pads' friction material, which can wear down over time, causing a squealing or grinding noise. \n\nIt's a good idea to have a professional mechanic take a closer look at your vehicle to determine the root cause of the issue. They can inspect the brake system and perform any necessary repairs to get your Camry stopping safely and smoothly. \n\nYou might also consider consulting the owner's manual or a repair manual for your specific vehicle make and model to see if there are any specific troubleshooting steps or recommendations for addressing this issue.",
