      "content": "The rhythmic quality of the noise is quite interesting. It's possible that you're dealing with a stuck or loose component that's causing the noise. One possibility is that a small piece of debris, such as a rock or a metal fragment, has gotten stuck in the brake caliper or rotor, causing the brake pads to vibrate and produce the noise. This is often referred to as a \"brake pad chatter\" or \"brake pad rattle\". \n\nIt's also possible that the brake caliper's piston or slide pins are stuck or corroded, causing the brake pads to vibrate and produce a rhythmic noise. This can be a bit more challenging to diagnose, but it's definitely a possibility. \n\nYou might want to try cleaning out the brake caliper and rotor to see if that resolves the issue. You can use a soft brush and some compressed air to clean out any debris that might be stuck in the mechanism. If the noise persists, it's still a good idea to have a professional mechanic take a closer look to determine the root cause of the issue.",
